title: Rouge Roubaix XVII Gran Fondo
description:
A gran fondo held on the classic 106 mile course of the Rouge Roubaix road race that covers the good, the bad, and the ugly of the Felicianaâ€™s.  This race is a classic test of man and his machine vs. the terrain and elements.

This is a fully supported Gran Fondo with vehicle support and 3 stocked SAG stops
course: The ride starts at 7:30am in St. Francisville, LA and travels north and west through the back roads of West Feliciana Parish and Wilkinson County, Mississippi. You will encounter a constantly rolling terrain, and a few climbs that will test all riders. The road surfaces will vary greatly. You will encounter chip and seal, sandy gravel, smooth as glass asphalt, and some roads that are just plain bad.
registration:
Registration online through BikeReg $115 + processing fee
Online Reg closes Thursday, March 13th at 11:45pm
Onsite registration and packet pickup at Magnusson Hotel on: 
Friday, March 13th from 5:00pm-8:00pm
Saturday, March 14th from 6:00am-7:15am
-Includes custom Rouge Roubaix T-shirt, Hoodie, Mussette, & Bottle
-$15 Local Food Vendor Credit for the weekend with every registration
-1 entry into Bike Raffle included with every registration
notes:
- Jersey's will be available for purchase
- Course will be open to traffic
- See event website for course map and more info
directions:
Starts from the Magnusson Hotel located in St. Francisville, LA

Address: 7059 US 61, 1 Lakeside Dr.
St. Francisville, LA 70775

description: Bike tour around the city of New Orleans. Riders can ride 20 miles or 40 miles. It will start and finish near Champion Square. There will be 3 rest areas along the course, post event party in Champion Square. Children must be at least 5 years old to participate.
course: Start and finish on LaSalle near Champion Square, tour through the French Quarter, Lakeview, and City Park.
registration: Registration is 10/16 at the downtown Hyatt from 10-7, Saturday is from 5am-7am near the start line. Entry fee is $60 until Oct 15, 11:59pm, at the expo is $75. VIP entry is $200 which includes bike jersey, lunch & breakfast.
directions: Start is at Poydras and LaSalle near the Mercedes Benz Superdome. Parking will be in the Superdome, $10 cash only.
